@startuml gridzoom_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #1a1a2e
skinparam defaultFontColor #e0e0e0
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #16213e
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #0f3460
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #e94560
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #533483
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #0f3460
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #16213e
skinparam noteBorderColor #533483
skinparam titleFontColor #e94560

title gridzoom — Hierarchical Visual Navigation Flow

actor LLM
participant "gridzoom" as gz
participant "screenshot" as ss
participant "SAM Server\n:18202" as sam
participant "mouse" as m
database "Session\n/tmp/gridzoom/" as db

== Capture (once per session) ==
LLM -> gz: capture -t chrome
gz -> ss: screenshot clean.png -t chrome
ss --> gz: hi-res image (1294x1399)
gz -> gz: resize to 1024px display\ndraw 10x10 chess grid\ncompute affine transform T
gz -> db: save clean + grid + metadata.json
gz --> LLM: image ID, grid file, cell coordinate map

== Zoom (crop from original, no re-grab) ==
LLM -> gz: zoom D4
note right: default +1 padding\n→ 3x3 region C3..E5
gz -> db: load root clean image
gz -> gz: crop region in original coords\nrescale to display size\nnew grid overlay\nnew transform T'
gz -> db: save child clean + grid + metadata
gz --> LLM: child ID, both images, coordinate map

== Resolve (pure math) ==
LLM -> gz: resolve B5
gz -> db: load image metadata
gz -> gz: cell B5 center → display coords\napply T' → original coords\n+ screen offset → screen coords
gz --> LLM: "394,468"

== Refine (SAM segmentation) ==
LLM -> gz: refine B5 -t chrome
gz -> db: load clean image for this level
gz -> gz: compute B5 center in display pixels
gz -> sam: POST /segment_point?x=385&y=466\n(image bytes)
sam --> gz: smallest segment at point\ncentroid=(404,456) bbox area=1800px
gz -> gz: map centroid through T' → window coords
gz -> m: mouse click 404,456 -t chrome
m --> gz: done
gz --> LLM: "clicked B5 → 404,456 (window: chrome)"

@enduml
